items.title: Using bcrypt on mac
items.body:
Sorry if I'm missing something obvious. I'm working with a `requirements.txt` that contains `bcrypt` and
`lambda-packages`.  I'm able to code this way on my mac.

I pip3 install this into a venv on my mac, and my code works.  When I `zappa update`  I see

```
Downloading and installing dependencies..
 - markupsafe==1.1.1: Using locally cached manylinux wheel
 - cffi==1.14.0: Using locally cached manylinux wheel
```

When I run the code on lambda I get an error on the `import bcrypt` line.  Am I using this package correctly?  Are the right packages getting into my zip file?

Thanks all!

items.title: Is this project still alive?
items.body:
Last merged PR is 1 year ago and 14 PR are waiting ...
The most urgent PRs are #95 and #106. Without them, people can't use latest version of Django with Zappa.

items.title: "ImportError: /var/task/psycopg2/_psycopg.so: invalid ELF header"
items.body: I haven't changed anything significant in my code but today I get this in lambda after doing zappa update.

items.title: PIL/Pillow not working with Python 2.7 on AWS Lambda
items.body: See my StackOverflow [post](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49903858/aws-lambda-using-pil-pillow-with-python-2-7) for information.

items.title: PyYAML
items.body:
Would a package of PyYAML be welcome in this repo? Is it better to use a pure python implementation of YAML in lambda to avoid this issue and if so, what's recommended?

If not, I can submit a PR with an Amazon linux built (with build steps in README) PyYAML package.

items.title: SQLite on Python 3 Lambda
items.body: Python3 lambdas don't have SQLite, even though it's part of the normal stdlib. We need to figure out how to package it in. May require another meta-package?

items.title: Cannot Update With PyPI
items.body: PyPI is becoming less and less friendly. Related: https://github.com/pypa/warehouse/issues/2342

items.title: Getting 'invalid ELF header' error on Lamba
items.body:
When I do a `zappa deploy dev` and call my API, I am getting this error:
`ImportError: /var/task/PIL/_imaging.so: invalid ELF header`

I am deploying from OSX. My guess is the precompiled binaries for OSX is being used by zappa on Lamba/Linux.

Did anyone run into something similar? How can it be fixed?

items.title: Support for pycrypto
items.body: Hello, I am interested in using pycrypto on AWS Lambda. If I am not mistaken, I can simply spin up a Amazon Linux EC2 instance and build the module and then upload for testing on Lambda, correct?. If so, I have no problem doing this myself and submitting a PR for the added package. Are there any caveats that I should be aware of? Thanks for your work on this and Django Zappa!

items.title: Lambda have a 50MB limit
items.body: Seems like Lambda have zip file package limit: http://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/limits.html

items.title: MySQL-python - don't follow README instructions, just untar and copy files to lambda folder
items.body:
following the readme instructions for `MySQL-python` doesn't work on amazon linux. 

instead, untarring the contents of the tar file and copying them does the trick.

by the way, thank you SO MUCH for this repo - was banging my head against the wall for hours trying to get this to work! :+1:

items.title: with lambda-packages installed, psycopg2 is still not actually available to zappa-based django deployment
items.body:
As far as I can see from the docs, I should be able to use psycopg2 with django-zappa now that lambda-packages is installed. This does not seem to be the case.Tailing the logs reveals:

`module initialization error: Error loading psycopg2 module: No module named psycopg`
